I am a Michigander, we toured Domino's Pizza as kids in elementary. I grew up on Domino's. I currently reside in Brooklyn and figured let's go to Domino's in which I live a 3 minute walking distance. Place an online order, after noticing on the tracking the bar wasn't moving about 10 minutes later I placed a call to confirm the order. The guy said 10 minutes👌! So I thought but I remind you the bar still hadn't changed until I called. The estimated pick was 8:28 - 8:38 pm. I get there approximately 8:40pm. The guy finally strolls over to the register I said hello, here for pick up. He says exactly "yeah, whats the name?" I said oh you don't say hello? He looked iritated, so I just gave him the name and then he asked my last four digits, I obliged, he fumbled I look up and the guy in the back three up 4 fingers, I assumed 4 minutes. He was so rude to the point where the child I was with said maybes he's tired. I explained to her thats no excuse if a customer comes into your store you greet them, and if someone says hello, you say hello back. Okay. 10 minutes later a lady in the back looks up front, and asked the guys in the back what are they still waiting on.  They shrugged, no sense of urgency or care in the world. She comes and asked what I ordered, my reply was huh? Ma'am I don't even remember at this point, and again she asked my four digits, in which I gave. 5 minutes later she comes out with my order. Silly me didn't bother to open the boxes to check, I assumed after all the time I waited it was going to be hot. Again I only live a 3 minute walk, literally two blocks behind the shop. Get home remove my outerwear, wash my hands, opened the box and had to put slices and wings in the oven. Oh by the way wings looked nothing like the pic online, it was literally salad dressing poured in top of the chicken, not tossed at all like it appears on the website. I called and the "manager" explained well of the customer isn't here for the time of pick up it goes in an oven to keep it warm. I explained to him I was there before the pizza was out of the oven, or before my order was "ready". He said well if you bring every thing back we"ll make you a new one. Okay I just told you I had to put the food in the microwave, were you listening? His response was there's nothing we can do. Goodbye.   Domino's you all need to make sure your franchisees are in compliance with Domino's Pizza, personally I will never go there again, not in NYC I am very dissappointed and appalled by the "managers" response. The worst service, to the point I had to explain to a child. I hope she, at least learned a lesson in customer service, because clearly  your franchisee was never taught. He act like I didn't have a choice, I'm sure they'll be other customers and my little $30 was just $30. But never again. Oh I am also going to do a Google review.
